First, separate the eggs. Yolk in one bowl, whites in the other bowl.


2Next, beat the egg whites until they are stiff.
3Put sugar in the bowl with yolk and mix.
4Pour milk into a pot and cook under medium heat. Stir occasionally.
5Pour the milk into the yolk and sugar mixture and mix well.
6Put it back into the pot until thick enough to make custard.
7Pour it into the mixed egg whites and mix.
8Now for the important part, add sea salt. Get a good balance between the sweet and salty. Do not add too much or you may get sick from the saltiness.
9Insert into the fridge to cool. While waiting, play Kingdom Hearts 2 or Birth by Sleep!
10Once the mixture is cooled, add cream and vanilla.
11Now add 12 drops of blue food coloring and three drops of green food coloring.
12Pour into the Popsicle molds and into the freezer or follow the instructions from your ice cream maker. Thank you for making sea salt ice cream. Just don't go on a high tower and eat it kids!

>>385537 (OP)
Milk in a bag comes in a few forms. One is the half gallon type that you would by for home use. There is a reusable pitcher that the bag goes in. This saves material in the manufacturing process, making it cheaper. Another type is the 2 to 5 gallon bag, this is used in many restaurants and they are put into large dispenser machines that use a weighted lever to close off the "hose" that comes out of the bag.

Milk in a bag comes in a few forms. One is the half gallon type that you would by for home use. There is a reusable pitcher that the bag goes in. This saves material in the manufacturing process, making it cheaper. Another type is the 2 to 5 gallon bag, this is used in many restaurants and they are put into large dispenser machines that use a weighted lever to close off the "hose" that comes out of the bag.

Another type is the 2 to 5 gallon bag, this is used in many restaurants and they are put into large dispenser machines that use a weighted lever to close off the "hose" that comes out of the bag.
